- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.

---------------------------

## Issue

I am trying to deploy three contracts to mainnet. Specifically, I am just deploying the contracts from [Ampleforth
s uFragments repo](https://github.com/ampleforth/uFragments) (I'm a new dapp dev trying to understand how everything works). For some reason no amount of gas works...it's either too big or too small. If I actually make it to the deployment phase, I end up seeing this error below after a few seconds:

```

Starting migrations...
======================
> Network name:    'mainnet'
> Network id:      1
> Block gas limit: 12481619 (0xbe7453)


1_deploy_contracts.js
=====================

   Deploying 'UFragments'
   ----------------------
   > transaction hash:    0x55c453e0a1e547aefaf5f71fcf8cf5548dbda77ddf85807b79b019744c4f7eaf
   â ¼ Blocks: 27           Seconds: 324Error [ERR_UNHANDLED_ERROR]: Unhandled error. ([object Object])
    at Web3ProviderEngine.emit (events.js:171:17)
    at self._getBlockByNumberWithRetry (/Users/megan/Documents/files/dev/defi/carrot/node_modules/@trufflesuite/web3-provider-engine/index.js:57:14)
    at afterRequest (/Users/megan/Documents/files/dev/defi/carrot/node_modules/@trufflesuite/web3-provider-engine/index.js:151:21)
    at _handleAsync (/Users/megan/Documents/files/dev/defi/carrot/node_modules/@trufflesuite/web3-provider-engine/index.js:176:21)
